# When two categories in a classification system are *structurally adjacent* (share surface-level signal but differ in load-bearing structure), curators systematically conflate them under cohort-pressure or threshold-clearance pressure. The conflation is a counter-instance to the discipline that prevents it; cataloging the conflation pattern produces a diagnostic tool.
lemma atom_0003_strand_conflation_failure_mode
