# A variant of Mechanism-C (institutional-universalizing transmission) where the institution preserves a body of work for centuries WITHOUT operational use, then a context-shift creates demand and the latent material activates. The institutional-preservation channel is necessary-but-not-sufficient; activation requires a downstream context that didn't exist at preservation time.
lemma atom_0004_latent_mechanism_c
  proves True
