# When a consequential review asks for judgment rather than mere implementation, run a second pass from a witness that does not see the first synthesis and is explicitly told not to agree by default; count convergence only if both passes reach comparable conclusions independently.
lemma atom_0010_blinded_independent_witness_pass
  proves True
